title: Oconomowoc boys soccer team gets another shutout
text:
Oconomowoc boys soccer team gets another shutout Oct. 22, 2015 11:53 p.m. (0) Comments 
Another victory, another shutout for Oconomowoc's boys soccer team. 
The Raccoons defeated Fond du Lac, 1-0, in a WIAA Division 1 regional semifinal Thursday at home. The victory was Oconomowoc's seventh straight shutout. 
Cole Doyle scored the match's only goal at 73 minutes. Josh Bobke got the shutout, but the defense only allowed a few chances. Bobke needed to make just one save. 
Milwaukee Bradley Tech 1, Milwaukee Pulaski 0: Josue Luna recorded six saves and got the shutout to help the Trojans advance. 
Germantown 2, Menomonee Falls 1: Ciaran Cummins' goal off a Ryan Mongan assist at 82 minutes was the game-winner for the Warhawks. Mongan scored Germantown's other goal at 56 minutes off a pass from Logan Turner. Division 2 
Cedarburg 2, Port Washington 1: The Bulldogs dispatched their North Shore rival thanks to a first-half score by Noel Baldwin and a second-half goal by Henry Brzycki. 
Wauwatosa East 3, Waukesha West 0: The Red Raiders got a goal and an assist from Ben Prange and Jalen Holley. 
Greendale 3, Pius XI 0: Mile Sever scored three goals in the first half for the Panthers. Division 3 
Delavan-Darien 5, St. Anthony 1: Tigrio Huerta recorded three goals and one assist for the defending state champion. 
Brown Deer 3, Waupun 2: Cameron Williams and John Pierson had one goal and one assists for the Falcons. GIRLS VOLLEYBALL Division 1 
West Allis Hale 3, Racine Horlick 1 : Taylor Supple finished with 25 kills for Hale in its 25-22, 24-26, 26-24, 25-23 victory. 
Pius XI 3, Milwaukee King 1: Cheyenne Henson had 15 kills for the Popes, a 25-19, 25-16, 22-25, 25-15 winner Division 3 
Lake Country Lutheran 3, Brookfield Academy 0: Brooke Andersen had 20 kills and 14 digs for Lutheran, which beat its Midwest Classic rival, 25-16, 25-20, 25-17. 
Mark Stewart
